Marketing tracking tool

Welcome to Marketing Tracking Tool documentation. Its purpose is to provide you information about REST API endpoints that may be used for development of third party apps. There are three types of Authentication keys:

  • admin - with full permission with expiration time 7 hours
  • user - with permissions to read statistics with expiration time 7 hours
  • web forms - with permissions to read entities and write leads and customers. Expiration time is set by admin.
  • api with read - has permissions to read entities and read and write leads and customers. Expiration time is set by admin. Use this key type carefully because you don't want to allow unauthorised parties to read customers data.

Response error types:

  • DATE_NOT_VALID
  • SLUG_NOT_UNIQUE
  • OBJECT_DOES_NOT_EXIST
  • INVALID_PAYLOAD
  • INVALID_CREDENTIALS
  • TOKEN_CREATION_FAILED
  • USER_NOT_FOUND
  • RESOURCE_NOT_AVAILABLE
  • WRITE_FILE_ERROR
  • DATABASE_ERROR
  • MIGRATIONS_ERROR
  • CREATE_PERMISSIONS_FAILED
  • OBJECT_DUPLICATED
  • OBJECT_CREATION_FAILED
  • EMAIL_NOT_UNIQUE
  • INTERNAL_VIOLATION
  • ID_NOT_UNIQUE
Language
  • cURL
  • jQuery
  • Ruby

API Keys

POST {{url}}/api/v1/api-keys
{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys

Create new API key for web form. Use read permissions extra carefully.

HEADERS
Authorization
Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type
application/json
BODY
{
    "name": "Forms",
    "description": "API key for forms",
    "expiration_date": "25-04-2202",
    "read_permissions": "true"
}


Sample Request
API key POST
curl --request POST \
  --url {{url}}/api/v1/api-keys \
  --header 'authorization: Bearer  {{token}}' \
  --header 'content-type: application/json' \
  --data '{\n    "name": "Forms",\n    "description": "API key for forms",\n    "expiration_date": "25-04-2202",\n    "read_permissions": "true"\n}'
var settings = {
  "async": true,
  "crossDomain": true,
  "url": "{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys",
  "method": "POST",
  "headers": {
    "authorization": "Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type": "application/json"
  },
  "processData": false,
  "data": "{\n    \"name\": \"Forms\",\n    \"description\": \"API key for forms\",\n    \"expiration_date\": \"25-04-2202\",\n    \"read_permissions\": \"true\"\n}"
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
  console.log(response);
});
require 'uri'
require 'net/http'

url = URI("{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys")

http = Net::HTTP.new(url.host, url.port)

request = Net::HTTP::Post.new(url)
request["authorization"] = 'Bearer  {{token}}'
request["content-type"] = 'application/json'
request.body = "{\n    \"name\": \"Forms\",\n    \"description\": \"API key for forms\",\n    \"expiration_date\": \"25-04-2202\",\n    \"read_permissions\": \"true\"\n}"

response = http.request(request)
puts response.read_body
import requests

url = "{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys"

payload = "{\n    \"name\": \"Forms\",\n    \"description\": \"API key for forms\",\n    \"expiration_date\": \"25-04-2202\",\n    \"read_permissions\": \"true\"\n}"
headers = {
    'authorization': "Bearer  {{token}}",
    'content-type': "application/json"
    }

response = requests.request("POST", url, data=payload, headers=headers)

print(response.text)
var http = require("http");

var options = {
  "method": "POST",
  "hostname": "",
  "port": null,
  "path": "{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys",
  "headers": {
    "authorization": "Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type": "application/json"
  }
};

var req = http.request(options, function (res) {
  var chunks = [];

  res.on("data", function (chunk) {
    chunks.push(chunk);
  });

  res.on("end", function () {
    var body = Buffer.concat(chunks);
    console.log(body.toString());
  });
});

req.write(JSON.stringify({ name: 'Forms',
  description: 'API key for forms',
  expiration_date: '25-04-2202',
  read_permissions: 'true' }));
req.end();
<?php

$curl = curl_init();

curl_setopt_array($curl, array(
  CURLOPT_URL => "{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys",
  CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
  CURLOPT_ENCODING => "",
  CURLOPT_MAXREDIRS => 10,
  CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 30,
  CURLOPT_HTTP_VERSION => CURL_HTTP_VERSION_1_1,
  CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST => "POST",
  CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => "{\n    \"name\": \"Forms\",\n    \"description\": \"API key for forms\",\n    \"expiration_date\": \"25-04-2202\",\n    \"read_permissions\": \"true\"\n}",
  CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => array(
    "authorization: Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type: application/json"
  ),
));

$response = curl_exec($curl);
$err = curl_error($curl);

curl_close($curl);

if ($err) {
  echo "cURL Error #:" . $err;
} else {
  echo $response;
}
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"strings"
	"net/http"
	"io/ioutil"
)

func main() {

	url := "{{url}}/api/v1/api-keys"

	payload := strings.NewReader("{\n    \"name\": \"Forms\",\n    \"description\": \"API key for forms\",\n    \"expiration_date\": \"25-04-2202\",\n    \"read_permissions\": \"true\"\n}")

	req, _ := http.NewRequest("POST", url, payload)

	req.Header.Add("authorization", "Bearer  {{token}}")
	req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json")

	res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)

	defer res.Body.Close()
	body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body)

	fmt.Println(res)
	fmt.Println(string(body))

}

POST {{url}}/api/v1/authenticate
{{url}}/api/v1/authenticate

Authenticates user and returns JWT Auth token. Authentication is valid for 7 hours.

HEADERS
Content-Type
application/json
BODY
{

    "password": "1234"

package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"strings"
	"net/http"
	"io/ioutil"
)

func main() {

	url := "{{url}}/api/v1/campaigns"

	payload := strings.NewReader("{\n    \"name\": \"My super campaign\",\n    \"description\": \"Tis is description of super campaign\",\n    \"slug\": \"my-campaign-2\",\n    \"expires_on\": \"2016-12-22 00:00:00\"\n}")

	req, _ := http.NewRequest("POST", url, payload)

	req.Header.Add("authorization", "Bearer  {{token}}")
	req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json")

	res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)

	defer res.Body.Close()
	body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body)

	fmt.Println(res)
	fmt.Println(string(body))

}

Customers management

POST {{url}}/api/v1/customers
{{url}}/api/v1/customers

Creates new customer for the provided lead Id. Lead Id preferably is a browser fingerprint. Email of the customer needs to be unique. As fields you can pass as many key -> value pair as you wish that will provide more information about the customer.

HEADERS
Authorization
Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type
application/json
BODY
{
    "lead_id": "a9aa445312aab6f75b4c98c455b8f820",
    "email": "aa@bbab.pl",
    "entity_id": 1,
    "fields": {
        "name": "Jack",
        "surname": "Doe",
        "phone_number": "+998877"
    }
}

  • post customer
  • customer post

payload = "{\n    \"lead_id\": \"a9aa445312aab6f75b4c98c455b8f820\",\n    \"email\": \"aa@bbab.pl\",\n    \"entity_id\": 1,\n    \"fields\": {\n        \"name\": \"Jack\",\n        \"surname\": \"Doe\",\n        \"phone_number\": \"+998877\"\n    }\n}"
headers = {
    'authorization': "Bearer  {{token}}",
    'content-type': "application/json"
    }

response = requests.request("POST", url, data=payload, headers=headers)

print(response.text)
var http = require("http");

var options = {
  "method": "POST",
  "hostname": "",
  "port": null,
  "path": "{{url}}/api/v1/customers",
  "headers": {
    "authorization": "Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type": "application/json"
  }
};

var req = http.request(options, function (res) {
  var chunks = [];

  res.on("data", function (chunk) {
    chunks.push(chunk);
  });

  res.on("end", function () {
    var body = Buffer.concat(chunks);
    console.log(body.toString());
  });
});

req.write(JSON.stringify({ lead_id: 'a9aa445312aab6f75b4c98c455b8f820',
  email: 'aa@bbab.pl',
  entity_id: 1,
  fields: { name: 'Jack', surname: 'Doe', phone_number: '+998877' } }));
req.end();

  CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => array(
    "authorization: Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type: application/json"
  ),
));

$response = curl_exec($curl);
$err = curl_error($curl);

curl_close($curl);

if ($err) {
  echo "cURL Error #:" . $err;
} else {
  echo $response;
}
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"strings"
	"net/http"
	"io/ioutil"
)

func main() {

	url := "{{url}}/api/v1/customers"

	payload := strings.NewReader("{\n    \"lead_id\": \"a9aa445312aab6f75b4c98c455b8f820\",\n    \"email\": \"aa@bbab.pl\",\n    \"entity_id\": 1,\n    \"fields\": {\n        \"name\": \"Jack\",\n        \"surname\": \"Doe\",\n        \"phone_number\": \"+998877\"\n    }\n}")

	req, _ := http.NewRequest("POST", url, payload)

	req.Header.Add("authorization", "Bearer  {{token}}")
	req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json")

	res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)

	defer res.Body.Close()
	body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body)

	fmt.Println(res)
	fmt.Println(string(body))

}

GET {{url}}/api/v1/customers?date_from={date}&date_to={date
{{url}}/api/v1/customers

Returns array of customers. If date_from and date_to are not provided retuns all customers from database.

HEADERS
Authorization
Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type
application/json


Sample Request
  • get customers
  • customers get
curl --request GET \
  --url {{url}}/api/v1/customers \
  --header 'authorization: Bearer  {{token}}' \
  --header 'content-type: application/json' \
  --data '{\n    "lead_id": "2",\n    "email": "aa@aa.pl",\n    "fields": {\n        "name": "Kris",\n        "surname": "Jack"\n    }\n}'

  "method": "PUT",
  "hostname": "",
  "port": null,
  "path": "{{url}}/api/v1/universities/2",
  "headers": {
    "authorization": "Bearer  {{token}}",
    "content-type": "application/json"
  }
};

var req = http.request(options, function (res) {
  var chunks = [];

  res.on("data", function (chunk) {
    chunks.push(chunk);
  });

  res.on("end", function () {
    var body = Buffer.concat(chunks);
    console.log(body.toString());
  });
});

req.write(JSON.stringify({ name: 'AGH Akademia',
  slug: 'agh-akademia',
  entity_slug: 'krakow' }));
req.end();

package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"strings"
	"net/http"
	"io/ioutil"
)

func main() {

	url := "{{url}}/api/v1/universities/2"

	payload := strings.NewReader("{\n    \"name\": \"AGH Akademia\",\n    \"slug\": \"agh-akademia\",\n    \"entity_slug\": \"krakow\"\n}")

	req, _ := http.NewRequest("PUT", url, payload)

	req.Header.Add("authorization", "Bearer  {{token}}")
	req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json")

	res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)

	defer res.Body.Close()
	body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body)

	fmt.Println(res)
	fmt.Println(string(body))

}
